rComments: very sweet and caring and understanding prof!

Ken somehow managed to make even the most boring material interesting and interactive in his lectures. There were only two assignments and an exam, but they were easy. If you're stuck on an assignment, go to his office hours and he gives SUCH helpful feedback! Hands down the best professor at this school; he genuinely cares about his students.

Ken Derry is simply an amazing prof! His lectures are super engaging and he engages with different teaching strategies so everyone has the opportunity to succeed. It's super easy to get a good mark in the class because he WANTS you to do well! I would take every single one of Ken's classes if I could

Professor Ken does an amazing job at teaching this class, he makes his lectures interesting and highly simplifies textbook material! I did really well in his class because I genuinely liked it very much. If you hate reading the textbook, make sure to attend the lectures as he gives really explanations + examples (very helpful for the exam)

I love Prof. Derry!!! I honestly only took this class because I needed a HUM course for my distribution requirements and had kinda low expectations. But his lectures are so fun. Hes super interactive in class and he explains theories in a simple way so that you can understand. If you attend lectures and attend ALL tutorials, youll do great.

He was amazing! I had him first year & he was the only prof who seemed to care about students. If you show up to every lecture/TUT you're guaranteed an A but you'll still do ok if you just keep up with the slides. His class was the only true Intro class at that school- giving us freedom to be creative & explore the topics that interest us most.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: took RLG101 with him. He is super nice, assignments aren't very hard, and marking is very reasonable (but depends on TA). If you do the readings and the assignments, you can easily get a good mark.
Lectures very boring. Makes you sleepy. Says a lot of uhmmmss. Not the best class and definitely wont recommend it.
Kindest prof I've had at U of T.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters']

rComments: Ken Derry is a great and very caring prof. Gives great feedback for essays, so be sure to stick around after lecture if you can't go to office hours. Is very engaging, uses many examples, and takes the time to learn students names. Textbook reading and lectures are somewhat optional but, tutorial attendance is not (attend all). Great prof overall!

Prof. Derry is one of the best at UTM! He's extremely passionate about religion and certainly, knows what he is talking about. Lecture slides get posted on the class website and it's better if you go to the actual lecture as he explains topics in more detail. Courseload isn't too bad if you stay on top of it. Overall, a great class with Prof. Derry

Really amazing prof!! Ken was so nice and supportive, humorous too! The class was interesting - the content is about Indigenous films and is okay (will depend on your take), but Ken made the class really inspirational with all the "aside" things that he talked about. Not even for the class, just for the prof, I'd say take his class! (Class at UTSG)
Ken is a very nice dude and he is definitely helpful when you have problems about the course.
Prof took us to so many temples and church to visit and know about the religions. I got much knowledge about the religion, which I did not know before
The best professor I've ever met.
Ken is so friendly and so nice. He likes to be with students and discuss their work.
Awesome professor and experience in Hong Kong Summer Abroad class! He is passionate about religion and the class was enjoyable. Field trips were such a great experience. Didnt exactly need readings
Good
Seemed alright at first. Ended up being a course that teaches about cultural marxism, rather than actual religion.

I personally didn't do well in the course because there was just soo much tutorial homework and i never made it to tutorials cause they were EARLYY mornings but nonetheless Ken is an awesome prof, he speaks with great energy and really encourages participation. emails often and keeps everyone up to date. awesome prof if you keep up with the work.

This course is very well structured and it is obvious that Derry cares about the students. He take time in lectures and office hours to learn the names of students. This course is writing-focused, as there are multiple writing assignments and homework that is due at each tutorial. Over half of the final exam was also writing based.

Derry is a good professor. I took RLG101 with him. He posts the lectures online so you dont have to go to class. The Final Exam was basically the same as the one last year, which is online might I add. Take the course for an easy A. On the Final exam, you get a crib sheet (cheat sheet). Its smooth sailing. Do the homework for tutorials!
Ken is an amazing prof! I loved having him and he completely knows what he's doing! We would chat during his office hours, and he always wants to have class discussions!
Amazing Professor! He really spent time to prepare his lectures and very enthusiastic. He taught first year students how to get into new life and introduced activities in campus. Highly recommend!
He taught me to think differently about things. Lectures are very interesting. He takes an unbiased and academic approach to learning about religions.
Amazing Prof! really cares about his students and wants them to succeed. His assignments are straight forward and he tells you exactly what he wants. You can get an easy A in the class Shoutout XO!

Amazing prof! I loved his lectures because they were so engaging and he loves when people participate in his class. He encourages his students to meet him during his office hours whenever you need help or even just to have a little chat. Do your readings and do the work and its an easy 4.0!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Participation matters']

rComments: Great prof. He's super friendly, funny, easygoing, and considerate of his students. Only two essays and one exam in the entire course, plus some easy tutorial stuff. Also, the textbook he uses is dirt cheap and he provides all the readings that are from his own book for free online. Highly recommend!

He's a really nice guy. I'm sad hes going on research leave. Would love to take more classes because he knows how to make university interesting and inspiring. In his class we learned not only about books but also about how to adapt and understand our lives and our future careers.
Weekly quizzes in tutorials on required readings and the assigned chapter. Super easy to do. No tests except exam. Don't need to attend lecture to succeed. He loves cats.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Group projects', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Awesome professor. Very funny and very easy going. Only have to do 2 essays and an exam for this course, easy A.
Love this class so much! Great prof, really funny and clear in his lectures.
Love this prof. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.

If you want someone to take you by the hand and walk you through the conundrum of your first year in university, this is the guy for you. He will show you the ways, he will teach you the ins and outs of survival. Great prof, always there even if you want to talk about stuff not related to his lecture.
The BEST PROF. Extremely kind, helpful, and caring! Very interesting lectures
replies to emails in seconds.
good prof okayy course.

I had him as my Prof. for first year religion and he was amazing. He was the nicest Professor. I had trouble writing an essay and he helped me so much. He was also the first Prof that I went to office hours for as a first year student and I was so nervous but he talked about movies to ease things up for me. So caring and friendly.

Cool prof, lectures are long and after a while get boring but DO NOT SKIP THEM as many multiple choice exam questions are essay based! Two essays which are marked fairly (depending on your TA). Tutorial quizzes and discussion board comments are easy marks so do the readings. Master past exams and you'll ace yours. GPA booster if you put in effort!
Great professor. Amazing lectures. Has a unique way of relating media to religion and got me thinking. He is a must have prof at UTM and is extremely helpful in any situation.

I feel like he goes way off topic. Tries to shove his own opinion about life down our throats. He doesn't allow us to have our own thinking. He is rude and constantly poses religion in a negative light.
He is an awesome professor that make you think in different ways.

Long lectures and often gets off topic. His assignments need to be more clear and needs to explain things in lectures instead of just showing pictures of unrelated things. He is not approachable and is often quite rude. He does not respect your opinion and will push his own opinions onto you. Got my credit and I'm done with him and the class.

Ken Derry was a great prof. Not my absolute fave but he was really great lecturer and was very clear. I hated the textbook because it was did not have very many headings or subtitles and had major blocks of reading. I thought the lectures were interesting. We had fun assignments, like to go to a place of worship and write about it.

Ken Derry is an excellent professor and makes it easy to do well in the course when you have a busy schedule. Other courses I've taken cost an arm and a leg when it comes to work load and time commitment.

I love Prof Derry!! He's such an approachable, and easy-going instructor. It's so hard not to like him! He makes class fun and intriguing. RLG101 was one of my favourite lectures to attend at UTM! Prof Derry is honestly the best! Just beware of the some of the TAs as they dictate how well you'll do in the course!

Professor Ken Derry is the awesomest professor at UTM!! This professor should definitely become Canada's prime minister or something ;). Too intelligent!! Don't ever hesitate to ask for help, he LOVES helping his students! We love you Dr. Ken Derry!
The sweetest man! Such a great prof.
Amazing Prof!
Professor Derry is a good prof, but the TAs' in this course are not. In terms grades it really depends on who your TA is.
He is pretty awesome & helpful.
great!

prof Derry is amazing. he is really funny and really cares about making the learning environment of students the best he can. he is really nice and friendly and he really makes the class fun. he covers all the material that is needed very clearly. he is a wonderful teacher.
Cutest Prof ever! He is so nice and considerate, I have never had a Prof like him before. It's impossible not to like him, and I really enjoyed his class. He is awesome :)!

Honestly, Prof. Derry is the absolutely one of a kind. He really cares for his students. He constantly delivers messages and answers all quires very quickly (I would e-mail him at 2 AM, and he'd reply back in 20 mins. #Awesome)...Anyways, he covers all material during his lectures. Mind you, the material very interested.

BEST. He is so helpful and he's funny and interesting and relevant. Has an entire lecture about Christianity and the Lion King... It doesn't get much cooler than that! Incredibly approachable and actually wants to help students. Very open and accepting of any criticism as well. Highly recommend anything he is involved with!
LOVED this class!

Honestly, he is the best first year prof ever. He seems to care a lot about his students, and will always be friendly when you approach him. He made the two hour lectures fun to sit through. Never a dull moment with this man. I would take the class again, and again if I could. Assignments and exam were completely fair. :)
Great Professor, I hope his contract of teaching at university of Toronto extends, Truly he is the most down to earth and best professor i have ever seen. Helpful to the max tooo

Good prof, keeps lectures entertaining. Not a fault of his, but tutorials are pretty useless but attendance counts toward your grade. Clear, helpful and nice perhaps to a fault. In a big class like RLG101 he ends up answering the same questions several times which is quite annoying if you actually listen to lectures
Great Prof, speaks clearly and his exam is a breeze
The best Professor ever; honestly you could not hope to getter a better prof then Ken Derry!!!

The sweetest prof ever!! Extremely helpful and approachable in class. He is  personable and thorough in his emails! Highly recommend taking his class- very interesting! Overall it was above and beyond my expectations! You will definitely learn something new!
Amazing prof! Engaging and super interesting! Allowed two tries on online quizzes, and allowed an one sheet aid (double sided) for final exam! Take his class, you won't regret it...hopefully.
Great professor! The course was extremely interesting and fair. Ken responded to all emails quickly with details. Overall AMAZING!

Nicest professor I've ever had. He is incredibly thoughtful, changes course material and deadline to suit students' preferences, and responds to each individual email extremely thoroughly. Great guy, and great sense of humour.
